{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:47:52.628730+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 80c6ad3f2330912d8cfabf6943b33205b9c5e93c)", "id": "lc_c314d9ac-d68f-4931-ad7b-82b408dbb48d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import { defineConfig } from 'vite';\nimport react  from '@vitejs/plugin-react';\nimport * as path from 'path';\nimport { existsSync } from 'fs';\nimport * as dotenv from 'dotenv';\n\n// Dotenv 是一个零依赖的模块，它能将环境变量中的变量从 .env 文件加载到 process.env 中\ndotenv.config({\n    path: existsSync('.env') ? '.env' : path.resolve('envs', `.env.${process.env.NODE_ENV}`)\n});\n\n// https://vitejs.dev/config/\nexport default defineConfig({\n    plugins: [react()],\n    resolve: {\n        alias: {\n            '@@': path.resolve(__dirname),\n            '@': path.resolve(__dirname, 'src')\n        }\n    },\n    server: {\n        cors: true,\n        port: process.env.VITE_PORT as unknown as number,\n        hmr: {\n            host: 'localhost',\n            protocol: 'ws',\n            port: process.env.VITE_PORT as unknown as number\n        }\n    }\n});\n", "id": "lc_edd2ffce-f61a-4ee7-aa12-25e041fac882"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "40054212-60a5-4634-973c-852fbc083f7d", "tool_call_id": "call_3c2d106fad6d46eebb28edc1", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:48:07.162809+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my analysis of the repository, here's what I found:\n\n## Package Manager\nThe repository expects contributors to use **Yarn**. Evidence:\n- There's a `yarn.lock` file in the root directory\n- The `Taskfile.yaml` shows `yarn install` and `yarn release` commands\n- The `package.json` has a script `\"fix\": \"yarn lint --fix\"` which explicitly uses yarn\n\n## Environment-Specific Scripts\n\nThe repository uses **cross-env** to set environment variables and **Vite** as the build tool. The environment-specific scripts in `package.json` are:\n\n**Development:**\n- `dev` - Runs local development server (`cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host`)\n- `dev:stg` - Runs staging development server (`cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite`)\n\n**Builds:**\n- `build` - Builds for production (`vite build --mode prod`)\n- `build:stg` - Builds for staging (`cross-env vite build --mode test`)\n- `build:prod` - Builds for production (`cross-env vite build --mode production`)\n\n**Environment Files:**\nThe repository has environment configuration files in the `envs/` directory:\n- `.env.local` - Local development environment\n- `.env.stg` - Staging environment  \n- `.env.prod` - Production environment\n\nThe `vite.config.ts` automatically loads the appropriate `.env` file based on the `NODE_ENV` environment variable set by cross-env.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 684, "prompt_tokens": 12333, "total_tokens": 13017, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 365, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11840, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000852159, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0